Detailed Description

Class RingerAudioDevice
Class to play ringer tones and other sound formats. All functions in this class deal with the ringer.
The ringer device can either be a traditional ringer or poly tone ringer from YAMAHA (MA2 or MA3).
The vibrator is also control through this class.

Note: Do not use audio interface given by the *AudioDevices* header files as they are outdated and will be removed.

enum RingerAudioDevice::Format
 

Sound formats.

Enumerator:
FormatSmaf  SMAF
MA2/MA3 NB: SMAF is not just SMAF. With the MA3 came extensions to the SMAF, which cannot be played on a MA2.
FormatMidi  MIDI
MA2/MA3 NB: Be aware that MIDI is many different formats, only following formats are supported: SP-MIDI, SMF format 0 and 1
FormatSmafPhrase11  SMAF phrasell - MA3.
FormatRmd  RMD - MA3.
FormatImelody  Imelody - MA3.
FormatBuzzer  Buzzer - MA3.

RingerAudioDevice::AudioReturnCode RingerAudioDevice::SetVolume (  RingerVolume  volume = RingerVolume3  ) 
 

Set the volume.
For the MA2/MA3 poly tone ringer 5 volume steps are available, for the buzzer only 3 volume steps (1, 3 and 5) If volume will not remembered after power off.

volume Volume to set

RingerAudioDevice::AudioReturnCode RingerAudioDevice::Start (  BOOLEAN  auto_release = TRUE  )  [virtual]
 

Plays the requested ringer tone.
The volume level will be last one selected AudioSetVolume method. If a ringer tone is started before the present one is finished, the present ringer tone will be disabled and the new ringer tone is started, i.e. no suspend/resume functionality.

See also:
GenericAudioDevice::Start
